<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="-1" COLOR="GREEN"><I>Rig Veda</I>, tr. by Ralph T.H. Griffith, [1896], at sacred-texts.com</FONT></P><HR></p>  <h3 align="center" align="center">HYMN CLXXXII. B&#7771;haspati.</h3>  
<p>1. B&#7770;HASPATI lead us safely over troubles and turn his evil thought against the sinner;<br> Repel the curse, and drive away ill-feeling, and give the sacrificer peace and comfort!<br> 2 May Nar&#257;&#347;a&#7745;sa aid us at Pray&#257;ja: blest be our Anuy&#257;ja at invokings.<br> May he repel the curse, and chase ill-feeling, and give the sacrificer peace and comfort.<br> 3 May he whose head is flaming burn the demons, haters of prayer, so that the arrow slay them.<br> May he repel the curse and chase ill-feeling, and give the sacrificer peace and comfort.</p>  
